description:
&lt;p&gt;We are very pleased to advertise a 0.4 fte Clinical/Counselling Psychologist 8a post within the inpatient services at Newham Centre for Mental Health. We are looking for enthusiastic and innovative individuals who are keen to bring psychological approaches to service users, carers and MDTs within the inpatient setting.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;The post holder would be primarily responsible for bringing psychological approaches to our two triage wards through individual and group therapy sessions, staff support via consultation, teaching, staff formulation and reflective practice sessions, and contributing to the wider hospital systems within the service and local community. The diverse population of service users accessing the hospital provides opportunities for creativity and innovation in engaging and facilitating psychological interventions. The acute psychology service aims to provide a high quality, equitable and culturally competent service to people with acute and highly complex needs. We look forward to welcoming the successful candidate, their ideas and passions into our team.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt; &lt;/p&gt;
